### Bug type

Regression (worked before, now fails)

### Summary

After switching from `azure-openai/gpt-5.2` to `azure-openai-responses/gpt-5.3-codex`, the agent intermittently says it will execute a task but returns plain text without issuing any tool call.

### Steps to reproduce

1. Use OpenClaw with `azure-openai-responses/gpt-5.3-codex` as the active model.
2. Send a tool-oriented instruction (example: “Please call a tool to get voice content”).
3. Check the session JSONL log for that turn.
4. Repeat the same instruction multiple times.
5. Observe that some turns produce `toolCall`/`toolUse`, while others produce only text (`stopReason: "stop"`) even when the assistant says it will proceed.

### Expected behavior

When the assistant commits to an action (“I will do X now”), it should emit at least one tool call (or explicitly refuse/ask for missing requirements without claiming it is already proceeding).

### Actual behavior

Intermittently, the assistant replies with commitment text (e.g., “I will now find/run...”) but no tool call is emitted in that turn.

### OpenClaw version

2026.3.2

### Operating system

Debian GNU/Linux 11 (bullseye)

### Install method

npm global install

### Logs, screenshots, and evidence

